The White House Office of the Press Secretary issued a statement in support of the Bipartisan Congressional Trade Priorities Act of 2014. The statement highlights the importance of Trade Promotion Authority in increasing exports and creating more American jobs. The United States aims to lower trade barriers that hinder the export of American goods and services. The statement emphasizes the need to seize opportunities and set high standards globally to prevent a race to the bottom. The White House is committed to working with Congress to renew the Generalized System of Preferences Program and strengthen Trade Adjustment Assistance for American workers.